  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7029.79 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +11.4B gamma wall at 7050, dealers are likely buying this dip as they're short gamma below current levels and need to hedge long deltas. The recent wall break event combined with the -7.5% five-minute move suggests we just punched through a key level, but the PIN regime and proximity to the 7030 (+9.0B) and 7035 (+7.6B) gamma walls should provide stabilizing buying pressure. Watch for bounce attempts into the 7050 mega-wall where dealers will turn sellers, with 7000 (+9.5B) as the next major support if we continue lower.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce attempt toward 7050 where selling pressure kicks in.",
